+## 📌 CVE-2000-0547 – Buffer Overflow in Kerberos 4 KDC
+
+- **Component:** Kerberos 4 Key Distribution Center (KDC)
+- **Issue:** Buffer overflow in the `process_v4` function due to improper bounds checking on the `localrealm` variable
+- **Impact:** Remote attackers could crash the service or potentially execute arbitrary code
+- **Upstream Status:** ❗ Affects **only legacy Kerberos 4**, which has been deprecated for decades  
+  → [MIT Kerberos](https://web.mit.edu/kerberos/)  
+  → [Alpine Security Tracker – No Entry Found](https://security.alpinelinux.org)
+
+### Vulnerable Versions (Alpine)
+| Release   | Package      | Status       |
+|-----------|--------------|--------------|
+| 3.18      | krb5-libs    | Not Affected |
+
+---
+
+### Why You Can't Fix This
+
+- ✅ **Kerberos 4** is not part of Alpine Linux; only modern **Kerberos 5** is included
+- ✅ The vulnerable `process_v4` function existed only in the **Kerberos 4 KDC**, removed long ago
+- ✅ **Alpine uses musl libc**, incompatible with older Kerberos 4 assumptions and build scripts
+- ✅ Alpine’s `krb5` packages are built from **current MIT Kerberos 5**, which do not contain the vulnerable code
+- ✅ **Alpine's CVE tracker has no entry** for CVE-2000-0547 — meaning it never shipped affected code
+
+**✅ Recommendation:**  
+This CVE is a **false positive** for Alpine 3.18 and other modern releases. No fix is necessary because the affected code never existed in Alpine packages.
+
+---
+
+## Summary
+
+- CVE-2000-0547 is a buffer overflow affecting obsolete Kerberos 4 KDC implementations
+- Alpine Linux does not and never did ship Kerberos 4
+- The relevant code does not exist in Alpine’s `krb5-libs` or any other package
+- Mark this CVE as **not applicable** to Alpine Linux and exclude it from vulnerability remediation plans
+
